cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nExplain how Gradient Ascent is different from Gradient Descent. If you wanted to *maximize* $f(x) = \\sin(x)$, what would the update rule be?\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nGradient Ascent seeks the maximum. You change the subtraction to addition: $x_{n+1} = x_n + \\alpha f'(x_n)$. \nBy adding the gradient, you move *uphill* instead of downhill.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 11 (Multivariable Gradient Descent)")
